@Node ABANDONSHIP "STCCG.guide/Glossary/Abandon Ship!"
@TOC MAIN
@INDEX INDEX

  @{b}Abandon Ship!@{ub}

For this dilemma, a ship's RANGE is considered reduced
if it is affected by a card that says that its RANGE is
reduced (Baryon Buildup), is -X (Vole Infestation) or
is "@{"disabled" link "XXPATH:glossary.guide/DISABLED"}" ("Pup"). A ship "cannot move" (Menthar
Booby Trap) is not considered to have its RANGE reduced.
The presence of a RANGE enhancement card does not negate
a RANGE reduction for this dilemma. For example, a ship
with its RANGE -2 from a Baryon Buildup and +2 from a 
Plasmadyne Relay still has its RANGE reduced. A ship is
damaged if it has any @{"damage" link "XXPATH:glossary.guide/DAMAGE"} markers on ot, or if it has
received "rotation damage".

You may choose which of your personnel will fullfill the
staffing requirements of your ship. A {command} personnel
may be choosen to cover a {staff} requirement. A ship
with "no staffing requirements" requires any one
appropriate personnel to staff it (see @{"ship staffing" link "XXPATH:glossary.guide/SHIPSTAFF"}). The
number of personnel required to staff the ship is a "group
limit" subject to the group limit modification rules. See
@{"dual-personnel cards" link "XXPATH:glossary.guide/DUALPERS"}.

Rescuing or @{"capturing" link "XXPATH:glossary.guide/CAPTURE"} the abandoned personnel is a game action.
You may not rescue your abandoned personnel during your
mission attempt. The personnel cannot be rescued by a 
docked ship. You may not capture your opponent's abandoned
personnel during his turn.

@Endnode

@Node ABDUCTION "STCCG.guide/Glossary/abduction"
@TOC MAIN
@INDEX INDEX

  @{b}abduction@{ub}

Cards such as Assimilate Counterpart and the Talon Drone
(Three of Nineteen) allow your Borg to abduct a personnel during
personal combat. When this happens, both combatants cease to
participate in the battle and may immediately beam away (if
possible), but are still "stopped".

The abducted personnel is consisted to be escorted by your Borg
present. On later turns you may move it around (like equipment). If
the abducted personnel is ever unescorted, your opponent can rescue
them with his own personnel present.

Abducted personnel are @{"disabled" link "XXPATH:glossary.guide/DISABLED"}, and do not participate in battles.
They are not considered captives and thus may not be rescued by the
Rescue Captives card. An abducted personnel who becomes
assimilated is no longer considered abducted.

@Endnode

