@Node BONUSAREA "STCCG.guide/Glossary/Bonus Point Area"
@TOC MAIN
@INDEX INDEX

  @{b}Bonus Point Area@{ub}

When you score points from any card with a @{"point box" link "XXPATH:glossary.guide/POINTBOX"},
that card (unless it remains on a target) is placed in a "bonus point
area" near your discard pile, as a reminder of those points, even if the
card says to discard it. This is not part of your discard pile and is
unaffected by cards such as Res-Q, Fire Sculptor etc.

If points are scored from a card without a point box (such as Lack of
Preparation), that card is discarded when resolved, not placed in the
point area. You must keep track of such points by another method.

